.TH RTIMULibDrive11 1
.
.SH NAME
RTIMULibDrive11 \- Command line demo for the Sense HAT IMU
.
.
.SH SYNOPSIS
.SY RTIMULibDrive11
.YS
.
.
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B RTIMULibDrive11
is a command line demonstration of querying the IMU (and some of the
environmental sensors) on the Raspberry Pi Sense HAT. It has no command line
options, and once started just continually prints the current orientation
("pose") determined by the IMU, along with the atmospheric pressure and
humidity.
.PP
The IMU should have valid calibration data (read from \(lqRTIMULib.ini\(rq if
available), as generated by
.B RTIMULibCal
otherwise the "pose" is likely to be extremely unreliable.
.
.
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR RTIMULibCal (1)
